";s:13:"label_endnote";s:1263:"%0 Report
%T The Meeting Graph : a New Framework for Loop Register Allocation
%+ Compilation (CHARME)
%A Eisenbeis, Christine
%A Lelait, Sylvain
%A Marmol, Bruno, P
%Z Projet CHARME
%N RR-2758
%I INRIA
%8 1995
%D 1995
%K GRAPH COLORING
%K GRAPH DECOMPOSITION
%K INSTRUCTION-LEVEL PARALLELISM
%K REGISTER ALLOCATION
%K LOOP OPTIMIZATION
%Z Computer Science [cs]/Other [cs.OH]Reports
%X Register allocation is a compiler phase where the gains can be essential in achieving performance on new architectures exploiting instruction level parallelism. We focus our attention on loops and improve the existing methods by introducing a new kind of graph. We model loop unrolling and register allocation together in a common framework, called the {\em meeting graph}. We expect that our results improve significantly loop register allocation while keeping the amount of code replication low. As a byproduct, we present an optimal algorithm for allocating loop variables to a rotating register file, as well as a new heuristic for loop variables spilling.
%G English
